text: When we use the Google Search, the search is done on the scikit learn website instead of Nisl.
title: Google search is on scikit-learn

text:
> @GaelVaroquaux : do you know the procedure or can I just create a new free
> account for the search engine ?

I think that you should create one.

Have a look at Jakes astronomy tutorial.. He used the Scikit-learn template for his tut and his google bar appears to search his content, not Scikit-Learn.

It's over here: [AstroML:  Machine Learning and Data Mining for Astronomy](http://astroml.github.com/#)
